 > English > Investor Relations > Anti-Fraud














                        Investor Room
Whistleblower Program








                    Anti-Fraud






                        As a public company listed on NASDAQ, Actions is obligated to maintain comprehensive
                        corporate governance practices and comply with the Sarbanes-Oxley Acts of 2002.
                        We have established a whistleblower program for our stakeholders, including the
                        management and staff, shareholders, clients, vendors, etc., to report any incidents
                        of fraud relating to Actions Semiconductor. Any stakeholder who becomes aware of
                        any potential incident of fraud, should report such incident directly to the Audit
                        Committee of Actions through:
                    


                            a. Regular mail:
                        

                               &nbsp Att: Mr. Casper Lin

                               &nbsp No.1,Ke Ji Si Road, Technology Innovation Coast of Hi-Tech
                            Zone, Zhuhai, Guangdong, China
                        

                               &nbsp Chairman of Audit Committee


                            or


                           b. E-mail:

                               &nbsp anti-fraud@actions-semi.com



Anti-fraud policy










                    Conflict Minerals Policy






                        As a public company listed on NASDAQ, Actions is committed to ensuring that the
                        materials used in Actions’ supply chain are sourced in an ethical and responsible
                        manner. We have established a whistleblower program for our stakeholders, including
                        the management and staff, shareholders, clients, vendors, etc., to report improper
                        activities in violation of the Conflict Minerals Policy or the Conflict Minerals
                        Rules relating to Actions Semiconductor. Any stakeholder who becomes aware of such
                        activities, should report such incident directly to the Audit Committee of Actions
                        through:
                    


                        a. Regular mail:
                        

                               &nbsp Att: Mr. Casper Lin

                               &nbsp No.1,Ke Ji Si Road, Technology Innovation Coast of Hi-Tech
                            Zone, Zhuhai, Guangdong, China
                        

                               &nbsp Chairman of Audit Committee


                            or


                           b. E-mail:

                               &nbsp anti-fraud@actions-semi.com



Conflict Minerals Policy



























































