Turning Signal Integrity Inside Out






























Turning Signal Integrity Inside Out














WHAT DOES IT MEAN TO TURN SIGNAL INTEGRITY
                SIMULATION INSIDE OUT?






> Today's electronics requires more than circuit analysis






> Physics-based simulation supported by circuit and system simulation
                rather than the other way around






> Assembly techniques eliminate errors and accelerates the design
                process 
              






> Automation leads to design innovation






Download our whitepaper now























Zoltan J. Cendes is IEEE fellow and the founder of Ansoft Corporation
                (acquired by ANSYS, Inc. in 2008). Cendes has made significant
                contributions in the area of finite element modeling of electromagnetic
                fields. In particular, introducing a number of new technologies
                in numerical electromagnetics including Delaunay tessellation;
                adaptive mesh refinement; edge elements; tangential vector elements;
                the transfinite element method; and model order reduction.





















Founded in 1970, ANSYS employs nearly 3,000 professionals, many of
              whom are expert M.S. and Ph.D.-level engineers in finite element
              analysis, computational fluid dynamics, electronics, semiconductors,
              embedded software and design optimization. Our exceptional staff
              is passionate about pushing the limits of world-class simulation
              technology so our customers can turn their design concepts into successful,
              innovative products faster and at lower cost.  As a measure
              of our success in attaining these goals, ANSYS has been recognized
              as one of the world’s most innovative companies by prestigious publications
              such as Bloomberg Businessweek and FORTUNE magazines.














Electronic products have evolved to the point where 3D electromagnetic
                  effects can no longer be ignored. 




The design flow must have the physics as primary and supported
                  by circuits. 





Turning Signal Integrity Inside Out White Paper:



















